## R2 — Serper API Structure (MEDIUM)

**Endpoints:**
- `POST https://google.serper.dev/places` — primary for local business discovery
  - Body: `{"q": "HVAC company Minneapolis MN", "gl": "us", "hl": "en", "num": 10}`
  - Response fields: `title`, `address`, `latitude`, `longitude`, `rating`, `ratingCount`, `category`, `phoneNumber`, `website`, `cid`
- `POST https://google.serper.dev/search` — for web results + `"location": "Minneapolis, MN"`
  - Response fields: `organic[].title`, `organic[].link`, `organic[].snippet`, `knowledgeGraph.title/website/phone`

**Free tier:** 2,500 queries total (no expiry clock on credits). $50 for 50K additional.

**Query strategy for MN industries:**
```python
queries = [
    "bowling alleys Minneapolis MN",
    "advertising agencies St. Paul MN",
    "HVAC contractor Bloomington MN",
    "dental clinic Edina MN",
    "craft brewery Minneapolis MN",
    ...
]
# POST to /places per query; deduplicate by cid or (name + address)
```

