## R3 — Apollo / Proxycurl API (MEDIUM) — CRITICAL CHANGE

**Proxycurl is SHUT DOWN.** LinkedIn sued them January 2025; they ceased operations. Do NOT reference Proxycurl in the build.

**Use Apollo.io instead:**

People Search (free, no credits consumed):
```
POST https://api.apollo.io/v1/people/search
Headers: x-api-key: <APOLLO_API_KEY>
Body: {
  "person_titles": ["CEO", "Owner", "Founder", "VP Marketing", "CTO"],
  "organization_name": "Acme Plumbing",
  "person_locations": ["Minneapolis, Minnesota"]
}
```
Response shape:
```json
{
  "people": [{
    "id": "...",
    "first_name": "Jane",
    "last_name": "D***",       // masked on free tier
    "name": "Jane D.",
    "title": "Owner",
    "linkedin_url": "https://linkedin.com/in/janed",
    "organization_id": "...",
    "organization": {
      "name": "Acme Plumbing",
      "website_url": "https://acmeplumbing.com",
      "estimated_num_employees": 15
    }
  }],
  "total_entries": 1,
  "page": 1
}
```

People Enrichment (costs credits, returns email):
```
POST https://api.apollo.io/v1/people/match
Body: { "first_name": "Jane", "organization_name": "Acme Plumbing", "reveal_personal_emails": false }
Response adds: email (if credits available), phone_numbers[]
```

**Free tier:** People search = free (no credits). Enrichment = limited monthly credits.
**DM card fields for drill-down UI:** `name`, `title`, `linkedin_url`, `organization.name`. Email shown only if enrichment credits available; gray out if absent.

